Topological Reconstruction Framework

==================================================
STATUS
==================================================

Research framework.

Coordinate system for open reconstructive systems.

This document distinguishes:

- External Consistency
- Axioms
- Definitions
- Derived Theorems
- Conditional Theorems
- Implications
- Hypotheses

Structural incompleteness is expected.

The framework is evaluated by:

- explanatory compression
- reconstructability
- grounding
- predictive usefulness
- generation of novel hypotheses
- structural ablation resistance

The framework does not claim that its axioms are self-evident.

The axioms are proposed because they exhibit substantial external consistency across multiple independently observed domains.

